Government departments seem to be uncertain regarding upcoming lockdown regulations. Earlier two major briefings were cancelled to allow for clarity on certain issues. Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu spoke to eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu has clarified the delayed briefing from the National Coronavirus Command Council on level three regulations. On Wednesday two major briefings were cancelled to allow for clarity on certain issues. Mthembu says the council needed to include regulations that President Cyril Ramaphosa announced. Lockdown regulations: Two major government briefings postponed Ramaphosa on Tuesday said that places of worship may reopen subject to strict restrictions under level three of the lockdown. Mthembu has apologised to South Africans for the delay. The country will move to level threeÂ on 1 June. The briefing will take place on Thursday at 2pm